==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predial
<hw>Pre"di*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praedium</ets> a farm, estate: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧dial</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of land or
farms; landed; <as>as, <ex>predial</ex> estate</as>; that is, real
estate.</def> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attached to land or farms; <as>as, <ex>predial</ex>
slaves</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Issuing or derived from land; <as>as,
<ex>predial</ex> tithes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prediastolic</ent>⟦br⟧
